# Floating dock chrome

All dock interaction and painting live in `atlas-shell::dock` (see `DOCK.md`).
Apps only supply `DockItem` lists and panel bodies.

## Hover (unified)

- **Label chip** (Action + Dashboard): always **above** the spawning icon on
  bottom docks (`icon_popover_anchor` + `Align2::CENTER_BOTTOM`). Never use
  egui `on_hover_text` for dock icons — it is inconsistent and draws below.
- **Dashboard description**: fade in over `describe_fade_duration` after
  `dashboard_describe_delay` — no hard show/hide layout jumps.
- **Tool / Dashboard body preview**: opens **on-icon** while hovering (not in
  the centered stack). Ease-in via `panel_open_duration` + `ease_out_cubic`.
  Previews survive the pointer's travel into the panel; they retire after
  `close_delay` once abandoned, never mid-flight.
- **Pinned panels only** join the centered stack layout.

## Persistence

Pinned panels are persistent palettes: outside clicks / Escape never unpin
(only re-clicking the icon does), and pins persist across sessions via
`floating_dock`'s `restore_pins` + `dock::pinned_ids` + `ChromePrefs`.

## Motion

Opening, pinning, and stack repositioning must use short ease-out motion
(tokens: `panel_open_duration`, optional future slide). Avoid instant pop or
layout snaps unless the user toggles a preference.

## Extension

New dock capabilities belong in `atlas-shell` so File Atlas and Slate stay
identical. Tune via `[dock]` in `ui-tokens.toml` / UI tuner.
